title: New 'Star Wars' trailer on 'Monday Night Football,' online
text:
HONS New 'Star Wars' trailer on 'Monday Night Football,' online 
This undated photo provided by Disney shows the poster for the new film, "Star Wars: The Force Awakens." "Star Wars" fans eagerly await the latest trailer for "The Force Awakens," airing during halftime of "Monday Night Football," on Oct. 19, 2015. The game starts at 5:15 p.m. PDT/8:15 p.m. EDT. (Disney via AP) Posted: Monday, October 19, 2015 8:16 pm | Updated: 12:01 am, Tue Oct 20, 2015. New 'Star Wars' trailer on 'Monday Night Football,' online Associated Press | 
LOS ANGELES (AP) — The Giants/Eagles game took a backseat to "Monday Night Football's" main event — the halftime premiere of a new "Star Wars: The Force Awakens" trailer. It also went online moments after. 
The 2:35 minute spot offered teases into the backstories of the series' newest characters, like John Boyega's Finn, a stormtrooper who's questioning his allegiances, Daisy Ridley's scavenger Rey, seen exploring an old ship, and Adam Driver's Darth Vader-obsessed Kylo Ren.
